# Resume Layout Requirements

## Page Structure

- Length: Exactly 1 page
- Layout: Single-column only
- Fonts: Arial, Calibri, Helvetica
- Font Size:
  - Body: 10–11 pt
  - Headings: 12–14 pt
- Margins: 0.5–1 inch
- Export format: PDF

---

# Resume Section Order

## 1. Header (No “Header” Title)

Format:

YOUR FULL NAME
Location, India | Phone | Email | LinkedIn | GitHub | Portfolio

Rules:
- Clean
- Compact
- No icons
- No excessive spacing

---

## 2. Professional Summary (Max 4 Lines)

Requirements:
- Fresher-appropriate
- Technical
- Specific
- No generic buzzwords
- Mention strongest engineering focus areas
- Align naturally with JD

Avoid:
- “passionate developer”
- “hardworking individual”
- “team player”
- generic fluff

---

## 3. Technical Skills

Place near top for ATS scanning.

Group by categories.

Example:

Technical Skills
- Languages: Python, Java, JavaScript, SQL, C++
- Frameworks & Libraries: React.js, Node.js, Express.js, FastAPI, Tailwind CSS
- Databases: MongoDB, MySQL
- Tools & Platforms: Git, GitHub, Docker, AWS EC2/S3, VS Code
- Core CS Concepts: DSA, OOP, DBMS, Operating Systems, Computer Networks

Rules:
- Mention only skills supported by evidence.
- Avoid listing technologies barely used.
- Be honest about proficiency.

---

## 4. Education

Compact format.

Template:

Bachelor of Technology (B.Tech) in Computer Science & Engineering
College Name, City | Expected Graduation: 2026 | CGPA: X.XX/10

Class XII | Board | Year | Percentage
Class X | Board | Year | Percentage/CGPA

---

## 5. Projects (Most Important Section)

Rules:
- Maximum 4 projects
- Maximum 6 bullets per project
- Maximum 2 lines per bullet
- Prioritise strongest projects first
- Include GitHub links

Bullet formula:
Action + Implementation + Tech + Impact

Strong bullet examples:
- Developed RESTful APIs using Express.js and MongoDB for user and product management workflows.
- Implemented JWT-based authentication middleware with protected routes and hashed password storage.
- Integrated file upload handling using Multer and cloud image hosting APIs.
- Containerized backend services using Docker for reproducible local deployment.
- Built automation scripts to process GitHub repositories and extract structured code metadata.

Avoid:
- “Created beautiful UI”
- “Used React for frontend”
- vague statements
- unverifiable metrics

